milligrams per liter (0.7 mg/L) for three (3) consecutive months, the public water system
may resume quarterly laboratory analysis for fluoride.
(c) This part does not prohibit naturally occurring fluoride in the water supply;
provided, that fluoride levels do not exceed the maximum levels permitted by federal law
or federal regulations, or seven-tenths milligrams per liter (0.7 mg/L), whichever is less.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-221-708(c), is amended by
deleting the subsection and substituting:
(c) A public water system fluoridating its water supply on or after May 1, 2025,
shall:
(1) Reduce the addition of fluoride or fluoride components to the water
supply, to comply with ยง 68-221-709, no later than July 31, 2025; and
(2) Provide written notice to their customers informing them of the
reduction of fluoridation and specify the date on which fluoridation will be
reduced. The notice must be issued thirty (30) days prior to the reduction of
fluoridation.
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 68-221-711, is amended by adding
the following new subdivision:
(10) The addition of fluoride, or a fluoride compound to the public drinking water
supply by the operator of a water supply system in this state that will result in the
drinking water supply reaching a level greater than seven-tenths milligrams per liter (0.7
mg/L), as well as levels seventy-five hundredths milligrams per liter (0.75 mg/L) or
greater for sixty (60) consecutive days. A violation of either level is considered a
separate violation.
SECTION 4. This act takes effect May 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it.
